text: Machine learning is a subset of artificial intelligence
Deep learning uses neural networks with many layers
Natural language processing handles text data
Computer vision enables machines to understand images
Reinforcement learning learns from rewards and penalties
Supervised learning uses labeled training data
Unsupervised learning finds patterns in unlabeled data
Transfer learning reuses models trained on other tasks
Generative AI creates new content like text and images
Large language models are trained on massive text corpora
Transformers use attention mechanisms for sequence modeling
BERT is a bidirectional transformer model
Embeddings represent words as dense vectors
Semantic search finds conceptually similar documents
Vector databases store and query embeddings efficiently
RAG combines retrieval with language generation
Fine-tuning adapts pretrained models to specific tasks
Prompt engineering designs effective LLM inputs
Tokenization splits text into processable units
